-- Bilfinger Agrees to Buy Water Tech Firm Johnson Screens
-- B y   J u r j e n   v a n   d e   P o l
-- 2013-01-18T12:19:25Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-01-18/bilfinger-agrees-to-buy-water-tech-firm-johnson-screens.html
Bilfinger SE (GBF) ,  Germany ’s second-
largest construction company by revenue, said it agreed to
acquire the U.S. water treatment group Johnson Screens Inc. to
expand in the industry. Terms weren’t disclosed.  The Mannheim-based company said today in a statement that
Johnson Screens, a provider of industrial filters and water well
screens since 1904, has revenue of about 160 million euros ($214
million) a year and employs 1,200 workers.  The New Brighton, Minnesota-based company specializes in
liquid and solid filtration and screening solutions for water
infrastructure and fluids processing.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jurjen van de Pol in Frankfurt at 
 jvandepol@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
